<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the MOST significant impact of the Spanish Flu pandemic on American society?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Changes in public health policy and medical research</option>
            <option letter="b">Disruption of the American military effort in WWI</option>
            <option letter="c">Acceleration of women entering the medical profession</option>
            <option letter="d">Economic losses from widespread business closures</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>While the pandemic had multiple effects, its most lasting impact was the transformation of American public health systems. The crisis led to the creation of new local health departments, expanded federal health research, and revolutionized how diseases were tracked and treated. Military disruption was temporary, women's medical roles had already expanded due to WWI, and the economic effects were overshadowed by post-war prosperity.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
